OL,6,FThe defendant, who cannot be named
OL,7,Fbecause of his age, was joined by his
OL,8,Ffamily at the hearing, where he
OL,9,Fentered two guilty pleas and the
OL,10,Fprosecution delivered a summary of the
OL,11,Ffacts.
OL,13,FCrown Advocate Peter Connick for the
OL,14,Fprosecution said the teenager had
OL,15,Fpaced the perimeter of the school
OL,16,Fwearing a balaclava fashioned from a t-
OL,17,Fshirt and was determined to get in.
